reviews.text: No ticket machine, no parking, impossible to cross to the second platform 10 minutes before a train arrives, so come super early

Has a basic two-hourly train service, hourly at peak times. No ticket machine, no parking and not used much except by those living within walking distance (such as me). Was on Beeching's hit list -how did it escape? Small car waiting area next to the level crossing for those picking up passengers -ignore the double yellow lines here, they were a mistake.
